properties.headline: Wind Chill Warning issued January 27 at 4:37AM AKST until January 29 at 6:00PM AKST by NWS Fairbanks, AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Dangerously cold wind chills of 60 to 70 below occuring.
The dangerously cold wind chills will cause frostbite in as
little as 10 minutes to exposed skin.

* WHERE...Northeastern Brooks Range in passes.

* WHEN...Now to 6 PM Wednesday.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Dangerously cold wind chills in passes are
expected to continue through Wednesday.
properties.instruction:
A Wind Chill Warning means the combination of very cold air and
sustained wind speeds of 15 mph or more will create dangerously
low wind chill values. Frost bite can occur quickly and even
hypothermia or death if precautions are not taken.

NWSheadline: WIND CHILL WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 PM AKST WEDNESDAY
